abstract: The political outsider did not get pledged delegates (or a boost) from Iowa and is in need of money and momentum. Can Granite State voters keep his campaign viable?
snippet: The political outsider did not get pledged delegates (or a boost) from Iowa and is in need of money and momentum. Can Granite State voters keep his campaign viable?
lead_paragraph: EXETER, N.H. — They say all politics is local. And for many months, the entrepreneur Andrew Yang has been dutifully reminding New Hampshire voters that he went to high school at Phillips Exeter Academy.

abstract: The point of the attacks was not to set off mass defections between the left and the center, but rather to consolidate support on one side of the party or the other.

lead_paragraph: HOOKSETT, N.H. — Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont and former Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., clashed throughout the day on Sunday, in a combative display of their determination to treat the upcoming New Hampshire primary as a two-person race, with former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. continuing to struggle.

abstract: With decision time just two days away, scores of New Hampshire voters on Sunday — and some political tourists — flocked to school gyms and hotel ballrooms to get a glimpse of the Democratic candidates as they made their closing arguments

abstract: If your preferred candidate doesn’t win the nomination, will you still do everything you can to deny Trump a second term?
snippet: If your preferred candidate doesn’t win the nomination, will you still do everything you can to deny Trump a second term?
lead_paragraph: It’s been a rough week for Democrats. President Trump is preening over his acquittal, his poll numbers and the economy, while the Democratic nomination race looks like a divided mess. Many Democratic voters are anxious that they have no great candidates, only those guaranteed to alienate one half of the party or the other.

abstract: Errors in the results have led The Times and others to refrain from calling the race, and the Sanders campaign manager said a partial recanvass of precincts could change the outcome.
snippet: Errors in the results have led The Times and others to refrain from calling the race, and the Sanders campaign manager said a partial recanvass of precincts could change the outcome.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Nearly a full week after the Iowa caucuses, the state Democratic Party on Sunday released results indicating that Pete Buttigieg, the former mayor of South Bend, Ind., was the winner after it updated data from 55 precincts. But errors in the result tabulations have led several news organizations, including The New York Times, to refrain from calling the race.

abstract: Chris Malloy runs a small events business in New Hampshire. The week before the state’s primary election, he has handled almost every campaign event.
snippet: Chris Malloy runs a small events business in New Hampshire. The week before the state’s primary election, he has handled almost every campaign event.
lead_paragraph: MILFORD, N.H. — The better Chris Malloy does his job, the less people will notice him. In fact, they might only know he had been there if things had gone terribly wrong.

abstract: Hosted by RuPaul and featuring Justin Bieber as musical guest, this week’s show also had another memorable Oscar segment.
snippet: Hosted by RuPaul and featuring Justin Bieber as musical guest, this week’s show also had another memorable Oscar segment.
lead_paragraph: It was a week in which President Trump was acquitted in his impeachment trial in the Senate and gave his annual State of the Union address, and the results of the Democratic caucuses in Iowa descended into chaos, delays and recrimination. So, naturally, “Saturday Night Live” began with … a parody of the Democratic debate in New Hampshire.

headline_main: ‘S.N.L.’ Takes Aim at the Democratic Debate and Trump’s Acquittal

abstract: Elizabeth Warren would have liked more speaking time at the debate. Amy Klobuchar said she had a home-field advantage at an ice arena. Both spent the day after making the case that they’re the ones to defeat President Trump.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren would have liked more speaking time at the debate. Amy Klobuchar said she had a home-field advantage at an ice arena. Both spent the day after making the case that they’re the ones to defeat President Trump.
lead_paragraph: HANOVER, N.H. — There is some disagreement on whether the post-debate glow of Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota should be called “Klomentum” or a “Klobucharge,” but whatever the terminology — she had it Saturday afternoon.

headline_main: They’ve Both ‘Won Every Race’ So Far, and Want a Win in New Hampshire
headline_print_headline: For Warren and Klobuchar, a Test of Winning Records
byline_original: By Astead W. Herndon and Shane Goldmacher

abstract: The former vice president and his campaign, under pressure after his poor performance in Iowa, mounted unusually personal attacks on Mr. Buttigieg ahead of the New Hampshire primary.
snippet: The former vice president and his campaign, under pressure after his poor performance in Iowa, mounted unusually personal attacks on Mr. Buttigieg ahead of the New Hampshire primary.
lead_paragraph: DOVER, N.H. — Tensions in the Democratic presidential primary reached new heights on Saturday as former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and former Mayor Pete Buttigieg clashed over experience in their most pointed confrontation to date, while Senator Bernie Sanders lashed both Mr. Buttigieg and another opponent, Michael R. Bloomberg, on the final weekend before the New Hampshire primary.
